  "body": "I've been trying to optimise my bundle and it seems to me that the standard react import `import React from 'react'` includes more code for backwards compatibility than react itself.\n\nI've found that including react this way `import React from 'react/lib/ReactIsomorphic` reduces my bundle size from ~177kb to ~77kb.\n\nCan this be documented or better supported? It's a significant gain. Or have some standard way to import only react that isn't going to break in future updates.\n",
